{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:51:01.054047+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6d39a0b3ffedb4da136abb7c078b7b47e11c272a)", "id": "lc_334be1d8-9cc6-4eea-9dea-d1a02de39f39"}, {"type": "text", "text": "version: \"3.7\"\n\nservices:\n  unit:\n    build:\n      context: ..\n      dockerfile: api/Dockerfile\n      target: test\n    environment:\n      - DB_STRING=postgresql://postgres:test@ci_db:5432/postgres\n\n  integration:\n    depends_on:\n      - ci_db\n    build:\n      context: ..\n      dockerfile: api/Dockerfile\n      target: test\n    environment:\n      - DB_STRING=postgresql://postgres:test@ci_db:5432/postgres\n\n  ci_db:\n    image: postgres:14.5\n    environment:\n      - POSTGRES_PASSWORD=test\n", "id": "lc_5ed632f5-4f3d-424f-a9ae-a07e0974f746"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b474d122-a751-496e-aa87-ec1dd98cc902", "tool_call_id": "call_0116ff812f804aa4a99addc8", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:51:01.070878+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ba1c5897d4ec62c411a8be5067cab9a227aaf7f5)", "id": "lc_a0c6f8fb-2217-4941-8a48-13bf982096ac"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import os\nimport time\n\nimport alembic.config\nimport pytest\nfrom sqlalchemy.exc import DataError, IntegrityError\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import sessionmaker\nfrom starlette.testclient import TestClient\n\nfrom api.main import app\nfrom api.repository import (\n    SQL_BASE,\n    InMemoryTodoRepository,\n    SQLTodoRepository,\n    Todo,\n    TodoFilter,\n    TodoRepository,\n    get_engine,\n)\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef fake_todo_repository():\n    return InMemoryTodoRepository()\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef todo_repository():\n    time.sleep(1)\n    alembicArgs = [\"--raiseerr\", \"upgrade\", \"head\"]\n    alembic.config.main(argv=alembicArgs)\n\n    engine = get_engine(os.getenv(\"DB_STRING\"))\n    session = sessionmaker(bind=engine)()\n\n    yield SQLTodoRepository(session)\n\n    session.close()\n\n    sessionmaker(bind=engine, autocommit=True)().execute(\n        \";\".join([f\"TRUNCATE TABLE {t} CASCADE\" for t in SQL_BASE.metadata.tables])\n    )\n\n\n@pytest.mark.unit\ndef test_example_unit_test():\n    assert 1 != 0\n\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_contract_test(fake_todo_repository: TodoRepository, todo_repository: TodoRepository):\n    \"\"\"See https://martinfowler.com/bliki/ContractTest.html\"\"\"\n\n    todo = Todo(key=\"testkey\", value=\"testvalue\")\n\n    for repo in [fake_todo_repository, todo_repository]:\n        repo.save(todo)\n\n        new_todo = repo.get_by_key(\"testkey\")\n        assert new_todo and new_todo.value == \"testvalue\"\n\n        assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(key_contains=\"e\"))) == 1\n        assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(key_contains=\"e\", limit=0))) == 0\n        assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(key_contains=\"v\"))) == 0\n\n        assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(value_contains=\"v\"))) == 1\n        assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(value_contains=\"e\", limit=0))) == 0\n        assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(value_contains=\"k\"))) == 0\n\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_repository(todo_repository: SQLTodoRepository):\n    with todo_repository as r:\n        r.save(Todo(key=\"testkey\", value=\"testvalue\"))\n\n    todo = r.get_by_key(\"testkey\")\n    assert todo.value == \"testvalue\"\n\n    with pytest.raises(IntegrityError), todo_repository as r:\n        r.save(Todo(key=\"testkey\", value=\"not allowed: unique todo keys!\"))\n\n    with pytest.raises(DataError), todo_repository as r:\n        r.save(Todo(key=\"too long\", value=129 * \"x\"))\n\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_repository_filter(todo_repository: SQLTodoRepository):\n    with todo_repository as repo:\n        repo.save(Todo(key=\"testkey\", value=\"testvalue\"))\n        repo.save(Todo(key=\"abcde\", value=\"v\"))\n\n    todos = repo.get(TodoFilter(key_contains=\"test\"))\n    assert len(todos) == 1\n    assert todos[0].value == \"testvalue\"\n\n    todos = repo.get(TodoFilter(key_contains=\"abcde\"))\n    assert len(todos) == 1\n    assert todos[0].value == \"v\"\n\n    assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(key_contains=\"e\"))) == 2\n    assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(key_contains=\"e\", limit=1))) == 1\n    assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(value_contains=\"v\"))) == 2\n    assert len(repo.get(TodoFilter(done=True))) == 0\n\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_api():\n    time.sleep(1)\n    client = TestClient(app)\n    response = client.post(\"/create/testkey?value=testvalue\")\n\n    assert response.status_code == 201\n    response = client.get(\"/get/testkey\")\n\n    assert response.status_code == 200\n    assert response.json() == {\"key\": \"testkey\", \"value\": \"testvalue\", \"done\": False}\n\n    response = client.get(\"/get/wrong\")\n    assert response.status_code == 404\n", "id": "lc_6f1d483b-f96b-44d1-8026-efab6b0c39ef"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "d3918706-301d-497b-bd9f-a26f1812dd22", "tool_call_id": "call_9172306549eb4c809c92dc7c", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:51:17.084425+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture. Here's how testing is organized in this FastAPI template:\n\n---\n\n## Testing Organization\n\n### Separation by Pytest Markers\n\nThe project uses **pytest markers** to distinguish between unit and integration tests. In `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[tool.pytest.ini_options]\nmarkers = [\n    \"unit: mark a test as a unit test.\",\n    \"integration: mark test as an integration test.\",\n]\n```\n\nIndividual tests are decorated with `@pytest.mark.unit` or `@pytest.mark.integration` in `api/test_all.py`. Notably, all tests live in **a single file** (`api/test_all.py`); the separation is by marker, not by directory.\n\n- **Unit tests** — e.g. `test_example_unit_test` — are pure logic checks that need no database.\n- **Integration tests** — e.g. `test_contract_test`, `test_repository`, `test_repository_filter`, `test_api` — exercise the real PostgreSQL database (running Alembic migrations and using a `todo_repository` fixture that connects to Postgres via `DB_STRING`).\n\n### Two Docker Compose Profiles in `.ci/docker-compose.yml`\n\nBoth the `unit` and `integration` services build the same Docker image (targeting the `test` stage of `api/Dockerfile`). The key difference: **`integration` depends on a `ci_db` Postgres container**, while `unit` does not — so unit tests run without a database, and integration tests get a live Postgres instance.\n\n### Make Targets\n\n| Target | Command | What it does |\n|---|---|---|\n| **`test`** | *(phony: depends on `utest` + `itest`)* | Runs **both** unit and integration tests in sequence. |\n| **`utest`** | `$(ci-compose) run --rm unit pytest -m unit .` | Spins up the `unit` service (no DB) and runs only tests marked `@pytest.mark.unit`. |\n| **`itest`** | `$(ci-compose) run --rm integration pytest -m integration .` | Spins up the `integration` service **with** Postgres and runs only tests marked `@pytest.mark.integration`. |\n| **`cleantest`** | kill / down / build on the `.ci` compose stack | Tears down any leftover test containers before a fresh run. Both `utest` and `itest` depend on `cleantest`. |\n| **`done`** | depends on `check` + `test` | The \"pre-commit\" gate: runs linting (`pre-commit run -a`) then all tests. |\n\n### Summary of the Flow\n\n```\nmake test\n  ├── make utest          (cleantest → docker compose run unit pytest -m unit)\n  └── make itest          (cleantest → docker compose run integration pytest -m integration)\n                              └── ci_db (postgres:14.5) must be up\n```\n\nIn short: the separation is **marker-based** (`-m unit` / `-m integration` via pytest), the execution is **container-based** (two separate Docker Compose services, one with and one without a database), and the top-level `make test` target simply chains `utest` then `itest`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 723, "prompt_tokens": 10869, "total_tokens": 11592, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 23, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9600, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.001215585, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000586575, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00062901}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962661-sh7aIUGJl6M67VKKKlaF", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a5-92d0-7ba3-9dfa-bbe6fd1dd899-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10869, "output_tokens": 723, "total_tokens": 11592, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9600}, "output_token